.TH "enable_tcs_irq" 9 "enable_tcs_irq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
enable_tcs_irq \- Enable or disable interrupts on the given TCS.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" enable_tcs_irq
.BI "(struct rsc_drv *drv "  ","
.BI "int tcs_id "  ","
.BI "bool enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
The controller.
.IP "tcs_id" 12
The global ID of this TCS.
.IP "enable" 12
If true then enable; if false then disable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
We only ever call this when we borrow a wake TCS for an active-only
transfer. For active-only TCSes interrupts are always left enabled.
